hmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md` | 218 lines. Chinese. Defines scope: file read/write with offset, stat, batch ops, chunked transfer, directory ops, glob search, chmod. Includes route table, request/response structures, impact analysis, risk assessment, alternatives analysis, acceptance criteria. |\n| **AR-016 Design** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/design.md` | 74 lines. Skeleton template with TODO placeholders for architecture, data model, interfaces, error handling, testing strategy, deployment, implementation steps, future changes. |\n| **AR-016 Tasks** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md` | 23 lines. Skeleton template with TODO placeholders. |\n| **Full Design (design.md)** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | 1563 lines. Comprehensive design for AR-016 PicoD File Management API. Includes architecture diagrams, data flow, package layout, all handler specs, error handling matrix, test matrix, implementation phases. |\n| **Delta Spec** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` | 870 lines. Formal spec with Gherkin-style scenarios (GIVEN/WHEN/THEN) for all 11 file management routes, config extension, ReadFile, WriteFile, StatFile, DeleteFile, MoveFile, MkDir, SearchFiles, Chmod, chunked upload/download, path sanitization, error response format. |\n| **SDD Prompt** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` | 256 lines. Contains client-go library reference specs for code generation context. |\n| **Root Proposal** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` | 218 lines. AR-011: Router JWT Authentication and Signing. |\n| **Test Spec** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` | 29 lines. TDD specification with test cases for Workload Manager, Router, Store, PicoD, and Python SDK. |\n| **Project Context** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` | 45 lines. Architecture overview, tech stack, conventions. |\n\n**ST-3 references:** All tasks.md files from AR-002 through AR-016 reference \"Stage ST-3 (Design Complete)\" as their precondition. ST-3 appears to be the \"Design Complete\" stage in the project's workflow.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Go Modules and Packages Organization\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (Go 1.25.0)\n\n**Package structure under `pkg/`:**\n\n```\npkg/\n├── apis/\n│   └── runtime/\n│       └── v1alpha1/           -- Kubernetes CRD type definitions\n│           ├── doc.go          -- +k8s:deepcopy-gen=package, +groupName\n│           ├── groupversion_info.go  -- GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder\n│           ├── register.go     -- Kind metadata, Resource() helper\n│           ├── codeinterpreter_types.go  -- ProtocolType, TargetPort, AuthModeType\n│           ├── agent_type.go   -- AgentRuntime, AgentRuntimeSpec, SandboxTemplate, AgentRuntimeStatus\n│           └── zz_generated.deepcopy.go  -- Generated by controller-gen\n├── common/\n│   └── types/\n│       └── types.go            -- Type aliases: SandboxInfo = handler.SandboxInfo, constants for Kinds\n├── picod/                      -- In-sandbox daemon (PicoD)\n│   ├── auth.go                 -- AuthManager (JWT RS256 middleware)\n│   ├── config.go               -- Config struct, ParseFlags()\n│   ├── execute.go              -- ExecuteHandler (POST /api/execute)\n│   ├── files.go                -- File handlers (upload, list, download, sanitizePath)\n│   ├── server.go               -- Server struct, route registration, health check\n│   ├── types.go                -- Request/Response structs, constants\n│   └── *_test.go               -- Corresponding test files\n├── router/                     -- HTTP Router (session-aware proxy)\n│   ├── router.go               -- Router interface + implementation (pattern -> Backend)\n│   ├── server.go               -- Gin server, route registration, graceful shutdown\n│   ├── backend.go              -- Backend struct\n│   ├── config.go               -- Router config\n│   ├── proxy.go                -- Proxy logic\n│   ├── loadbalancer.go         -- Load balancer\n│   ├── session_manager.go      -- Session management\n│   ├── jwt.go                  -- JWTManager (token signing)\n│   ├── middleware.go           -- AuthMiddleware, ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware\n│   ├── informer.go             -- K8s informer integration\n│   ├── health.go               -- Health endpoints\n│   ├── errors.go               -- Error types\n│   └── *_test.go               -- Tests\n├── store/                      -- Session storage (Redis + Valkey)\n│   ├── store.go                -- Store interface (10 methods), ErrNotFound, Storage() singleton\n│   ├── store_redis.go          -- Redis backend (go-redis/v9)\n│   ├── store_valkey.go         -- Valkey backend (valkey-go)\n│   ├── singleton.go            -- sync.Once initialization, STORE_TYPE routing\n│   ├── codec.go                -- JSON encode/decode for SandboxInfo\n│   └── *_test.go               -- Tests (miniredis mock)\n└── workloadmanager/            -- K8s workload management\n    ├── handler/                -- HTTP handlers\n    │   ├── sandbox_create.go   -- Sandbox creation handler\n    │   ├── sandbox_delete.go   -- Sandbox deletion handler\n    │   ├── sandbox_lifecycle.go -- Lifecycle management\n    │   ├── models.go           -- Data models (SandboxInfo, EntryPoint)\n    │   └── constants.go        -- Constants\n    ├── middleware/              -- (empty directory)\n    ├── reconciler/              -- K8s reconciler\n    │   ├── reconciler.go       -- Main reconciler\n    │   ├── agentruntime.go     -- AgentRuntime reconciler\n    │   ├── codeinterpreter.go  -- CodeInterpreter reconciler\n    │   ├── pod.go              -- Pod reconciler\n    │   ├── sync.go             -- Sync logic\n    │   ├── event_handlers.go   -- K8s event handlers\n    │   ├── metrics.go          -- Prometheus metrics\n    │   └── types.go            -- Reconciler types\n    └── response/               -- HTTP response helpers\n        ├── response.go         -- SuccessResponse, ErrorResponse, JSON(), Created(), Error()\n        └── response_test.go    -- Tests\n```\n\n**Binary entry points under `cmd/`:**\n```\ncmd/\n└── picod/\n    └── main.go                 -- PicoD daemon entry point\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing API Patterns\n\nThe project uses **REST APIs exclusively** (no gRPC found). Two distinct API frameworks are used:\n\n#### Pattern A: Gin-based REST APIs (primary)\n\n**PicoD API** (`pkg/picod/server.go`):\n```\nGET  /health                     -- Health check (no auth)\nPOST /api/execute                -- Command execution (JWT auth)\nPOST /api/files                  -- File upload (JWT auth) -- multipart or JSON Base64\nGET  /api/files?path=            -- Directory listing (JWT auth)\nGET  /api/files/*path            -- File download (JWT auth) -- wildcard route\n```\n\n**Router API** (`pkg/router/server.go`):\n```\nGET  /health/live                -- Liveness probe (no auth)\nGET  /health/ready               -- Readiness probe (no auth)\nGET/POST /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path   -- Agent invoke (JWT + concurrency limit)\nGET/POST /v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path -- Code interpreter invoke (JWT + concurrency limit)\n```\n\n**Middleware stack (Router):** `gin.Logger()` -> `gin.Recovery()` -> `AuthMiddleware()` -> `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware()`\n\n**Middleware stack (PicoD):** `gin.Logger()` -> `gin.Recovery()` -> `AuthMiddleware()` (JWT RS256)\n\n#### API Response Patterns\n\n**PicoD error format** (inline in handlers):\n```json\n{\"error\": \"message\", \"code\": 400, \"detail\": \"details\"}\n```\n\n**WorkloadManager response format** (`pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go`):\n```go\ntype SuccessResponse struct {\n    Data    interface{} `json:\"data\"`\n    Message string      `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n}\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error     string `json:\"error\"`\n    Code      int    `json:\"code\"`\n    RequestID string `json:\"request_id,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\nHelper functions: `JSON()`, `Created()`, `Error()`, `ErrorWithID()`\n\n#### Key API Design Conventions\n\n1. **Authentication:** JWT RS256 with RSA public key from environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`\n2. **Path sanitization:** 4-layer workspace jail defense (EvalSymlinks + Rel check + prefix check + final EvalSymlinks)\n3. **Request binding:** Gin's `c.ShouldBindJSON()` with `binding:\"required\"` struct tags\n4. **Error responses:** Consistent JSON format with `error` and `code` fields\n5. **File content encoding:** Base64 for JSON-based file transfers\n6. **Body size limit:** 32 MiB (`http.MaxBytesReader`)\n7. **Timeout handling:** Default 60s, timeout exit code 124\n8. **Logging:** `klog/v2` exclusively (no `log.Printf`)\n9. **HTTP/2 support:** Router uses h2c for cleartext HTTP/2\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28790e1f0ffeqSz5pGZCS0pvm0","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775842041356,"end":1775842239091}}}}
